@page "/"
@using ColourTherapy
@inject AppSettings Settings

<PageTitle>Chromatherapy - Color Healing for Your Emotions</PageTitle>

<div class="home-container">
    <div class="card intro-card">
        <h2>Welcome to Chromatherapy</h2>
        <p class="lead">Discover the healing power of colors for emotional well-being</p>
        
        <div class="color-strip">
            <div style="background-color: #F9D949;"></div>
            <div style="background-color: #F88379;"></div>
            <div style="background-color: #ACCBE1;"></div>
            <div style="background-color: #C8A2C8;"></div>
            <div style="background-color: #90EE90;"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="intro-text">
            <p>Color therapy, also known as chromatherapy, is the practice of using colors to improve physical, 
            emotional, and mental well-being. Dating back to ancient Egypt, India, and China, this therapeutic 
            approach recognizes that specific colors can influence our mood, energy levels, and even physical state.</p>
            
            <p>Each color carries a unique frequency and vibration that can resonate with different aspects of our being. 
            By surrounding ourselves with particular colors, we can help balance our emotions and support healing.</p>

            <p>This application helps you discover colors that may benefit your current emotional state, along with 
            complementary flowers that carry similar healing properties.</p>
        </div>

        <a href="@($"{Settings.BasePath}/mood-selector")" class="btn btn-primary mt-4">Begin Your Color Journey</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .home-container {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        min-height: 70vh;
    }

    .intro-card {
        max-width: 800px;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .intro-text {
        text-align: left;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .lead {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .color-strip {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        height: 10px;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        border-radius: 5px;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .color-strip div {
        flex: 1;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .mt-4 {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
</style>
